Floating point arithmetic can&#39;t handle equality properly. I.e it might be
that
3/6!=1/2

Usually, one of them is 0.5, while the other one is 0.49999999999999

That&#39;s what the delta is for - it allows for an error margin. 1e-6 is fine
for me, most of the time. But it really depends on your domain what kind of
precision you&#39;re demanding.

Bye,
